<!-- SECTION 1 -->

<B>Original Summary</b>: The JDBC 4.0 API specification seeks to improve Java application access to SQL data stores by the provision of ease-of-development focused features and improvements at both the utility and API level. Using new Java language features planned for <a href="http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=176"> JSR-176</a> Java 2 Standard Edition 1.5, features such as annotations as defined in <a href="http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=175">JSR-175</a>, generics defined in <a href="http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=14">JSR-014</a> in to addition to supplying a set of JDBC utility classes, SQL savvy developers will be able to more easily access SQL data sources while still benefiting from the full power of the JDBC API.

<A NAME="1"></A>

